'''模方程'''（modular equation）是一個有[[模數|模數]]的[[代数方程|代数方程]]。給定一些在[[模空间|模空间]]中的函數，模方程是一些有關模空间函數的方程，或是一些有關模數的[[恆等式|恆等式]]。

最常見到的模方程是和[[椭圆曲线|椭圆曲线]]有關的模量問題。此處的模空间是一維的，因此表示若在模曲線的{{le|代數簇的函數域|function field of an algebraic variety|函數域}}有兩個[[有理函數|有理函數]]''F''及''G''，會滿足模方程''P''(''F'',''G'') = 0，''P''是二變數的非零[[复数_(数学)|複數]][[多項式|多項式]] 。若選擇了適當的，非退化的''F''和''G''，方程''P''(''X'',''Y'') = 0就會定義模曲線。
<!--
This can be qualified by saying that ''P'', in the worst case, will be of high degree and the plane curve it defines will have [[奇点_(数学)|Mathematical singularity]]; and the [[系数|coefficient]]s of ''P'' may be very large numbers. Further, the 'cusps' of the moduli problem, which are the points of the modular curve not corresponding to honest elliptic curves but degenerate cases, may be difficult to read off from knowledge of ''P''.

In that sense a modular equation becomes the '''equation of a modular curve'''. Such equations first arose in the theory of multiplication of [[橢圓函數|elliptic function]]s (geometrically, the ''n<sup>2</sup>''-fold [[covering_map|covering map]] from a 2-[[环面|torus]] to itself given by the mapping ''x'' → ''n''·''x'' on the underlying group) expressed in terms of [[複分析|complex analysis]].-->

